Tell us something more about the project

About us

Jamifind is an innovative platform for all level musicians, made by musicians. We want you to find the best possible collaboration partners for your music projects. Whether you're looking for a new member(s) to your band, random jamming company, the perfect music teacher, a producer that shares the same artistic view as you, a cellist to your studio sessions or any other music industry players like a lyricist or a composer, Jamifind will help you find them!

Our mission is to support and contribute to music culture by helping musicians and other music industry players connect with each other more easily and efficiently. We cherish self-fulfillment and encourage people to create music projects for everyone to enjoy.

The Best place to find band members

The spark that ignited the creation of Jamifind came from the realization that people are still using bulletin boards, old school web-forums or Facebook groups to find a missing bass player for their band or promote their music lessons business. These ads usually give little or no information on the person who is advertising: their background, music interests, skill level, education or the like. These are the problems we wanted to solve with Jamifind. And currently, there is no better place to find musicians that suit your needs.

Looking for a music teacher?

You always wanted to learn how to play the piano but were always too busy to make the effort to find a piano teacher that really works for you? Where would you start looking anyway? Not only is it time-consuming to go through all the possible music lesson providers out there, googling will only give you teachers that have their own websites. They are usually already fully-booked and might be located too far away from you.

Or maybe you are looking for beginner guitar lessons for your children? In that case, you probably want to be even more precise when selecting the person giving the music lessons. The small ads on the bulletin board of your local super market might not provide the best information for choosing the right music teacher.


Jamifind's first version features are:

  • Create your free musician's profile that works as your musicians resume
  • Add the instruments you play, other music-related skills and your level of competence
  • Add music via SoundCloud, video via YouTube and photos to your profile
  • Find other musicians or music teachers based on your search criteria (e.g. instrument and genre) and set the search distance
  • Browse suggested profiles using a grid or map view
  • Send and receive personal messages
  • Compatibility: Jamifind finds the best possible matches for you, using your favorite bands and other information you choose to fill into your profile. The more information you share on your profile, the better it works.
  • A shoutbox where you can share links to your projects like upcoming live events or music videos, have a chat with other users about today's hot topics etc.
  • Soon we will also be adding the first batch of music stores and live music bars / clubs on our map
  • Please invite your friends to join Jamifind too :)

We will be adding new features as we develop the service further and we will keep you updated about them.

We are working hard to make sure this site does all it can to help you find the talent you need for your musical pursuits. For us, it's all about bringing musicians together!

If you have any suggestions for updates or improvements to the site, please let us know. We value your input and look forward to it.
